5.
Question 5
If we wanted the loop to execute at least once even if the condition will never be true, we use:

1 / 1 point

For loop


While loop


Do While loop

Correct
Correct. The Do While loop will always execute the body of the loop first then check the condition second.

6.
Question 6
To stop the loop from going, even when the condition is true, we use:

1 / 1 point

stop;


continue;


break;

Correct
Correct. The Break statement forces the loop to stop.

7.
Question 7
The first element of any is at index 0:

1 / 1 point

True


False

Correct
Correct. In C++ the first element of the array will always be at index 0.

8.
Question 8
A Two-dimensional Array is an array of arrays:

1 / 1 point

True


False

Correct
Correct. Each element of a Two-dimensional array is itself an array.

9.
Question 9
To clear the console screen we use:

1 / 1 point

system(“cls”);


clear;


restart;

Correct
Correct. This command clears the entire console screen, cls is short for "clear screen"
